OL,3,CMore than 1,700 Brits taking legal
OL,4,Caction over Tui Cape Verde illnesses
OL,6,FMark Ashley travelled to Cape Verde
OL,7,Fwith his family in October 2025,
OL,8,Fexpecting a relaxing break, but became
OL,9,F"violently ill and never recovered",
OL,10,Fhis wife Emma, 55, said.
OL,12,FThree days into their holiday, he fell
OL,13,Fill with symptoms including stomach
OL,14,Fpains, diarrhoea, vomiting, fever, and
OL,15,Fextreme lethargy, Irwin Mitchell said.
OL,17,FOn their return to the UK, Ashley's
OL,18,Fsymptoms continued and he later
OL,19,Fcollapsed at home and was taken to the
OL,20,Fhospital on November 12. He was
OL,21,Fpronounced dead shortly after.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1775635511
OL,3,CMore than 1,700 Brits taking legal
OL,4,Caction over Tui Cape Verde illnesses
OL,6,FPooley, a retired mum-of-two from
OL,7,FLydney, travelled with a friend to the
OL,8,FRiu Funana resort on the island of Sal
OL,9,Fon October 7 for a fortnight's holiday
OL,10,Fcosting #3,000 and booked through Tui,
OL,11,Fthe law firm said.
OL,13,FShe became sick on October 11 with
OL,14,Fgastric symptoms, including diarrhoea,
OL,15,Fand in the early hours of the next
OL,16,Fday, she slipped on water leaking from
OL,17,Fa fridge while going to the bathroom,
OL,18,Fbreaking her leg.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1775635511
OL,3,CMore than 1,700 Brits taking legal
OL,4,Caction over Tui Cape Verde illnesses
OL,6,FShe was transferred to a local clinic,
OL,7,Fand over the next four days, continued
OL,8,Fto experience diarrhoea and vomiting,
OL,9,Fbefore she was airlifted to Tenerife
OL,10,Ffor urgent care on October 16.
OL,12,FPooley died the next day from multi-
OL,13,Forgan failure, sepsis and
OL,14,Fcardiorespiratory arrest, lawyers
OL,15,Fsaid.
OL,17,F"We're utterly heartbroken. Karen was
OL,18,Fthe kindest, loveliest person," her
OL,19,Fhusband Andy said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31812
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1775635511
OL,3,CMore than 1,700 Brits taking legal
OL,4,Caction over Tui Cape Verde illnesses
OL,6,F"She was a devoted wife and mum who
OL,7,Floved swimming, walking the dog in the
OL,8,FForest of Dean, and volunteered at a
OL,9,Flocal charity shop. She was also a
OL,10,Fwonderful friend who lit up every room
OL,11,Fshe entered."
OL,13,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,14,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,15,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,16,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,17,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,18,Fbelow...
